title: System Information Discovery via Systeminfo
id: 3542e151-866d-4afc-935c-07686d44a75c
status: experimental
description: |
    Detects system information discovery using systeminfo.exe.
    Three detection layers:
    1. Image field - standard execution
    2. OriginalFileName - catches renamed binary (evasion resistant)
    3. CommandLine - catches execution via cmd.exe scripts
    
    Attackers often run systeminfo after initial access to understand
    the target environment before lateral movement.
author: Mahesh Inna Kedage
date: 2026/05/03
references:
    - https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1082/
    - https://github.com/redcanaryco/atomic-red-team/tree/master/atomics/T1082
logsource:
    product: windows
    category: process_creation
detection:
    # Layer 1: Standard execution via image path
    selection_image:
        Image|endswith: '\systeminfo.exe'

    # Layer 2: Renamed binary - originalFileName in PE header
    # Cannot be changed without recompiling binary
    selection_original:
        OriginalFileName: 'sysinfo.exe'

    # Layer 3: Execution via commandLine (catches cmd.exe wrappers)
    selection_cmdline:
        CommandLine|contains: 'systeminfo'

    condition: selection_image or selection_original or selection_cmdline
falsepositives:
    - IT asset inventory scripts
    - System monitoring tools
    - Helpdesk diagnostic scripts
level: medium
tags:
    - attack.discovery
    - attack.t1082
